   &UR; REAL _  &LR; Determined not to become Microsoft road kill,
RealNetworks announced another major partnership yesterday aimed at
increasing distribution of its audio- and video-playing software.
By David Einstein
</P>
<P>
   &UR; COMPUTINGQ&AMP;A _  &LR; Question: I have a lot of documents on my old
Macintosh that I'd like to transfer into my new iMac. But how can I
do this, since the iMac has no floppy drive? By David Einstein
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NOTEBOOKS _  &LR; Anyone who has used a handheld PC knows the true
meaning of frustration. The screen is too small to offer more than
a token view of documents, and the keyboard is absurdly tiny. You
need the fingers of a 4-year-old to type comfortably.
</P>
<P>
   Relief is on the way, however. In the coming months, major
companies including Hewlett-Packard and Sharp will introduce the
next wave of handhelds, with bigger, sharper displays and nearly
normal-sized keyboards. By David Einstein
</P>
