<P>
   SUICIDE-ADVANCE _ The first National Conference on Suicide
Prevention meets in Reno, Nevada, this weekend, bringing together
450 activists, researchers, educators and public health
authorities. The meeting, conceived by Atlanta activists Jerry and
Elsie Weyrauch, is an unprecendented attempt to coordinate the
nation's suicide prevention efforts. A third of the people there
will be survivors, so it could be an emotional scene. Story will
summarize the weekend and advance the news conference, scheduled
for Tuesday in Atlanta, in which Surgeon General Satcher and others
discuss their course of action. (Auchmutey, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 50ish.
