</P>
<P>
   WOLFE-ATLANTA _ The Chamber of Commerce is not likely to put Tom
Wolfe's Atlanta novel ``A Man in Full'' on its required reading
list, but the city comes off a lot better than some Atlantans
feared. ``A Man in Full'' (Farrar, Straus and Giroux, $28.95)
begins in the heat of Freaknik and ends with the cool teachings of
the Greek Stoic philosopher Epictetus. In between, Wolfe uses a
broad brush to portray the sprawling, racially-mixed landscape of
the Southern boom town. The novel will not hit stores until Nov.
12, but reviewers were shipped advance copies on Monday. (O'Briant,
Atlanta JOurnal-Constitution). WITH PHOTO.
