</P>
<P>
   BLACKCHURCHES _ An alarming number of Black churches are
experiencing financial difficulties, younger church members are
more critical of church management, and African Americans belonging
to the Church of God in Christ, Pentecostal and Baptist
denominations tend to give more money than those of other
denominations. These are a few of the findings released today
(Wednesday, Oct. 21), part of a two-year study by the
Interdenominational Theological Center. (Blake, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
