physics are awarded to females. To Jadwiga Sebrechts this is a
gender gap. It's obviously a statistical difference _ you could
even say a gaping one _ but is it necessarily evidence of
injustice? Are young women not going into physics and chemistry
because the environment conditions them to look elsewhere? (Skube,
