<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following for
clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of Wednesday, Oct.
21, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please call Bob
Schenet at (206) 448-8037.
</P>
<P>
   NEA-IVEY (Undated) _ For the past several years, the National
Endowment for the Arts has been teetering on the brink of
execution, surrounded by enemies, deserted by friends. Those dark
days are over, William Ivey, the agency's new chairman,
emphatically declared in a phone interview from his office in
Washington, D.C.
</P>
<P>
   By R.M. Campbell. (Story will move in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
