<HEADLINE>
.
</HEADLINE>
  
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``e'' entertainment news file. For questions, contact Bob
McCarthy at the Daily News, (818) 713-3665. 
. 
BURNETT-SONDHEIM (Los Angeles) _ Carol Burnett says Stephen
Sondheim isn't one of her favorite composers. He IS her favorite.
Burnett takes over the lead female role previously played by Diana
Rigg and Julie Andrews in ``Putting It Together,'' the five-person,
all-Sondheim revue that opens Sunday at the Mark Taper Forum in Los
Angeles. By Reed Johnson. 
. 
SLAM-REVIEW (Los Angeles) _ Like sports in a number of ghetto
problem movies, poetry is held up as a route out of the cycle of
despair and violence in ``Slam,'' which takes the urban drama in a
strange but pleasing new direction. (3 stars) By David Bloom.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
TALKIN-RADIO (Los Angeles) _ As expected, dance-oriented Groove
103.1 flipped formats Monday afternoon to triple-A (adult album
alternative), and the station is looking nationwide for on-air
talent and personalities. By Fred Shuster. &QL;
</P>
