</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Christian compilation a pre-release hit
 &HT;    By Russ DeVault
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The rapidly growing sales of Christian music _ the '97 total was
$550 million _ will get another boost today with the arrival in
stores of ``WOW 1999,'' an all-star compilation from the Sparrow
Label Group that has shipped gold with advance orders for more than
500,000 units.
</P>
<P>
   With that many copies of the two-CD, 30-track set moved, the
Nashville-based Sparrow Label Group confidently predicts ``WOW
1999'' will surpass the '96 and '97 compilations, both of which
generated sales of more than 1 million. The participating artists
this year include dc Talk, Newsboys, Jars of Clay, Steven Curtis
Chapman, Michael W. Smith and Bob Carlisle, who drew in many
mainstream fans in '97 via his original crossover hit, ``Butterfly
Kisses.'' The two discs offer mildly disparate styles, with one CD
devoted to rock and alternative pop and the other to more
traditional pop and inspirational music.
</P>
<P>
   New in stores today
</P>
<P>
   -- Deana Carter, ``Everything's Gonna Be Alright'' (Capitol).
Country sensation's second release follows 4-million-selling album
and CMA single of the year, ``Did I Shave My Legs for This?''
</P>
<P>
   -- Jonny Lang, ``Wander This World'' (A&AMP;M). Guitar scorcher's
release duels with fellow young bluesy picker Derek Trucks' new
album.
</P>
<P>
   -- The Derek Trucks Band, ``Out of the Madness'' (House of
Blues).
</P>
<P>
   Recently reviewed
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Bizzy Bone, ``Heaven'z Movie'' (Ruthless Relativity).
Grade: C. (520)
</P>
<P>
   -- Bob Dylan, ``Live 1966 _ The `Royal Albert Hall' Concert.''
Grade: A. (722)
</P>
<P>
   -- Kiss, ``Psycho Circus'' (Mercury). Grade: A-. (433)
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
