 &HT;    SOUTHERN HAPPENINGS
 &HT;    By Paula Crouch Thrasher
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   -- Lumpkin , Ga._ Westville Village's annual Fair of 1850
features fall harvest activities, including syrup making and cotton
ginning, along with the town's daily antebellum-style operations.
Wagon rides, historical displays, boot making and pottery
demonstrations. 1-888-733-1850.
</P>
<P>
   -- Amelia Island, Fla. _ The fifth annual Heritage Classic Car
Celebration, Friday through Sunday, showcases more than 300 makes
and models of classic and vintage automobiles, trucks, motorcycles,
military vehicles and firetrucks lining Centre Street in historic
downtown Fernandina Beach. Also: food, antiques, art and cultural
heritage exhibits. 1-800-226-3542.
</P>
<P>
   -- Ferrum, Va. _ The Blue Ridge Folklife Festival on Saturday at
Ferrum College is the state's largest showcase of authentic
regional folk crafts, music, food and old-time competitions.
540-365-4416.
</P>
<P>
   -- New Market, Va. _ Heritage Days Fall Festival on Saturday and
Sunday brings Shenandoah Valley heritage to life with basketry,
apple butter boiling, arts and crafts, walking tours and a parade.
540-740-3212.
</P>
<P>
   -- Alexandria, Va. _ George Washington's Mount Vernon Estate and
Gardens transforms its four-acre pioneer farm site into a
Colonial-style festival for families Saturday and Sunday. Apple,
pumpkin and corn sampling, farming and Halloween activities.
703-780-2000.
</P>
<P>
   -- Charleston, S.C. _ The Preservation Society of Charleston
hosts the 22nd annual Fall Candlelight Tour of Homes and Gardens
through Saturday. Candlelight tours of various historic districts
are 7-10 p.m. Thursdays-Saturdays. $30. 1-800-968-8175.
</P>
<P>
   -- Beaufort, S.C. _ The Fall Festival of Houses and History
through Sunday features 18th- and 19th-century homes on the banks
of the Beaufort River in Carolina Lowcountry. 843-524-6334.
</P>
<P>
   -- Chattanooga, Tenn. _ The Fall Color Cruise and Folk Festival
is Saturday and Sunday, featuring a major arts and crafts show and
Tennessee River excursions on the Southern Belle riverboat.
1-800-322-3344.
</P>
<P>
   -- Pigeon Forge, Tenn. _ The Smoky Mountain Harvest Festival
through Nov. 1 features harvest decorations and the 19th annual
Pigeon Forge Rotary Club Crafts Fair (through Monday) in Patriot
Park and the Tennessee Crafts Fair (through Sunday) at the Grand
Resort Hotel and Convention Center. 1-800-251-9100.
</P>
<P>
   -- Tallulah Falls, Ga. _ Days for increased water flow through
Tallulah Gorge State Park will be today, Friday and Oct. 31. The
aesthetic flow releases will be 200 cubic feet per second compared
with 500 and 700 during white-water boating weekends. Hiking or
rappeling into the gorge during releases is prohibited; however,
views are available from the rim trail's overlooks. 706-754-7970 or
http://www.gastateparks.org.
</P>
