Nov. 1 spotlights traditional crafts, fall foods, autumn
decorations and Southern gospel music. 423-428-9488.
</P>
<P>
   -- Huntsville, Ala. _ ``The Red Clay Survey,'' a biennial juried
show, features 98 works by 63 Southern artists, from conceptual
pieces to traditional realism. At the Huntsville Museum of Art
through Sunday. 256-535-4350.
</P>
<P>
   -- Asheville, N.C. _ Biltmore Estate hosts the final weekend of
the second annual Michaelmas: An English Harvest Fair on Saturday
and Sunday. Arts and crafts, entertainment, children's activities,
archery demonstrations, a grape stomp and food and wine seminars.
1-800-323-6822.
</P>
