ARIZONA-WATER (Undated) - Water from municipal and private water
suppliers in Arizona is generally safe. But there are problems,
especially in rural areas. And the water generally doesn't taste
all that great out of the tap, which is why nearly 3 of every 4
Phoenix-area residents drinks either bottled or filtered water at
home. Although no one has died because of water contamination,
environmentalists contend Arizona's water supplies are accidents
waiting to happen. Coincidently, Phoenix area municipalities are in
the midst of a campaign to convince residents that their water is
good to drink. By STEVE YOZWIAK. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
