think of the Nobel Prizes as ``Masterpiece Theatre,'' think of the
Ig Nobels as The Larry Sanders Show.'' The work is still top-notch;
it's just that it's also funny. By BILL GOODYKOONTZ. Story will
move in the ``L'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
BOOK-AUTHOR (Undated) _ When Barbara Kingsolver was 7, her family
moved from its home in Kentucky to central Africa, where her
parents did public health work for a year. Now, 30 years later, she
has written a novel that is rooted in her time in Africa. ``The
Poisonwood Bible'' (Harper Flamingo, $26) is Kingsolver's most
political novel, built around the violent struggle for power in the
Congo and the role American interests played in it. By ANNE
STEPHENSON. Story moved in the ``E'' category. &QL; 
