<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    MindSpring shows bounce in its earnings
 &HT;    By Frances Katz
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ MindSpring Enterprises on Wednesday posted its fourth
consecutive profitable quarter and once again beat analysts'
forecasts. The company reported a profit of $4 million, or 15 cents
a share.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts surveyed by First Call had expected MindSpring to earn
11 cents a share. MindSpring closed Tuesday at $31.25, up $1.31
1/4. During the same period last year, MindSpring lost $627,000, or
3 cents a share.
</P>
<P>
   The Atlanta-based Internet service provider _ the largest ISP in
the Southeast and the largest independent ISP in the country _
reported third-quarter revenue of $28.7 million, vs. $14 million
for the same period last year. MindSpring's subscriber base
increased to 455,000, up from 393,000 in the previous quarter.
</P>
<P>
   ``We are proud of what MindSpring has accomplished to date,''
said company Chairman Charles Brewer in a statement. ``In the third
quarter we expanded our member base 16 percent from the prior
quarter while posting our fourth consecutive quarter of record
profits.''
</P>
<P>
   Commenting on the third quarter, MindSpring Vice President and
Chief Financial Officer Michael Misikoff, said: ``We are pleased
with the performance for the quarter and happy to see subscriber
growth increase over the quarter. We are also happy to see we were
able to contain costs and earn a little bit more per share than
people were expecting.''
</P>
<P>
   Misikoff said subscriber growth was due to dial-up membership
and Web hosting. Membership growth from the SpryNet acquisition
will show up in the fourth quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Looking ahead to the fourth quarter, Misikoff says the company
will face new challenges. A top priority is integrating subscribers
of the recently acquired SpryNet ISP into the MindSpring fold.
</P>
<P>
   ``We do have significant challenges facing us in the fourth
quarter,'' Misikoff said. ``We will have to successfully transition
SpryNe
</P>
</TEXT>
