u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BUDGET-SPOT-SPI &LR;      10-20 0197
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUDGET-SPOT-SPI </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Wednesday, Oct. 21
</P>
<P>
   and thereafter. If you have any questions, please call Bob
Schenet at 206-448-8037.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-JUSTICE (Washington) _ Comparing government lawyers to
``19th century reactionaries who ... went around smashing machines
with sledgehammers to arrest the march of progress,'' Microsoft
Tuesday launched its counterattack on the government's sweeping
anti-trust case.
</P>
<P>
   By Michael Paulson. (Story will move in the ``w'' category)
</P>
