   ITALY-DINING (Undated) _ There is no bad food in Italy. That may
be an exaggeration, but after three weeks of traveling there, I
have come to believe it is true. In small towns and big cities, in
tiny trattorias and even tourist restaurants, we ate well
everywhere. A Critic's Notebook. By Ruth Reichl.
</P>
